## Desarrollo Local

### 1. Configurar variables de entorno

Copiar `development/.env.sample` a `.env` en la raiz y completar:

```bash
ARTIFACTORY_USER=tu_usuario
ARTIFACTORY_PASSWORD=tu_password
```

### 2. Levantar infraestructura local

```bash
cd development/docker-local-ms
docker compose --env-file ../../.env up -d
```

Esto levanta:
- **LocalStack** (SSM Parameter Store{% if integrations.uses_s3 %}, S3{% endif %}{% if integrations.uses_sqs %}, SQS{% endif %})
- **Mock OAuth** (simula Cognito)
{% if observability.datadog_enabled %}
- **Datadog Agent** (modo no-forward, validacion de instrumentacion)
{% endif %}
- **App** (el microservicio compilado)

### 3. Verificar

- Swagger UI: [http://localhost:8080{{ context_path }}/swagger-ui.html](http://localhost:8080{{ context_path }}/swagger-ui.html)
- Health: [http://localhost:8080{{ context_path }}/actuator/health](http://localhost:8080{{ context_path }}/actuator/health)
- OpenAPI JSON: [http://localhost:8080{{ context_path }}{{ openapi_path }}](http://localhost:8080{{ context_path }}{{ openapi_path }})

### 4. Detener

```bash
cd development/docker-local-ms
./down.ps1   # Windows
./down.sh    # Unix
```

